THE recent spate of deadly attacks on KZN cops has claimed another policeman&rsquo;s life.In the latest attack, two off-duty cops were attacked by three armed men while seated outside their home in the Makhoso area of Mtwalume, on the south coast on Wednesday night.One of the two cops, who was stationed at Msinsini Police Station, died at the scene.Constable Siyabonga Mbele (28) sustained gunshot wounds to the chest, stomach and left thigh. His colleague escaped unharmed.Captain Nqobile Gwala, KZN cops spokesman, said the suspects took six cellphones, two State firearms, an Opel Astra vehicle and fled the scene.&ldquo;The incident occurred at approximately 8.30pm. The suspects demanded the cops&rsquo; firearms and fired shots towards them. &ldquo;The vehicle was recovered in Umlazi&rsquo;s M section later that night.&rdquo; She said charges of murder, attempted murder and armed robbery are being investigated by Hibberdene police. &ldquo;We are appealing to anyone who might have information on the whereabouts of the suspects to immediately contact the local police or our CrimeStop number on 08600 10111.&rdquo; Major-General Bheki Langa, the provincial acting commissioner, condemned the attack.